Preheat the oven to 200°C. Place the @diced butternut squash{300%g} on a large #baking tray{}, drizzle with a little @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Use your hands to coat the squash in the oil and seasoning. Arrange in a single layer on the tray, then pop on the top shelf of the oven to roast until tender and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn when you add the tomatoes later on.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over a medium-low heat. When hot, add the onion and pepper to the pan. Gently cook, stirring occasionally, until the peppers and onion are really soft, ~{15-20%minutes}.

In the meantime, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}(halved). Tear the @ciabatta{1} into small, bite-size pieces. Zest then halve the @lemon{1/2}. When the squash has been cooking for ~{10%minutes}, turn the squash then add the tomatoes to the tray with another drizzle of @oil{} if you need it. Gently mix and return to the oven for the remainder of the cooking time, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, make the dressing by combining the @olive oil{1%tbsp} (see ingredients for amount), parsley, lemon zest and half the lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, mix well and set aside. Put the ciabatta on another #baking tray{} with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of salt. Toss together and bake on the middle shelf of the oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Give the tray a shake halfway through.

When the peppers are soft, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Remove from the heat and add to the #bowl{} with the dressing. Do any washing up and when ready, remove the veggies and croutons from the oven, add to the bowl and gently mix. Let the bowl sit for a couple minutes (the ciabatta will absorb the flavours!).

Carefully fold the @wild rocket{40%g} into the bowl with the roasted veggies and croutons. Divide between plates and crumble the @feta cheese{100%g}(crumbled) over the top. Enjoy!

> We love a good Panzanella Salad with Butternut & Feta and this deliciously simple, chef-curated recipe doesn't disappoint. Time to bust out the pots and pans!